review": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ATBlxQ8Fm.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://www.breitbart.com/europe/2026/07/05/zelensky-and-putin-hold-separate-talks-with-president-trump/", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Zelenski and Putin hold separate talks with President Trump on ending the Russia Ukraine war.  ", "last_comment_created": 1783277213380, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 7, "score_up": 29, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Russian and Ukrainian leaders held separate calls with U.S. President Donald Trump on ending the war, now in its fifth year.", "large_image": "tD0BNHOknQL77h8H.png", "title": "Zelensky and Putin Hold Separate Talks With President Trump on Ending War"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBlxQPEk", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 23, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8714566, "raw_content": "\n\u201cBut you are not in the flesh but in the Spirit, if indeed the Spirit of God dwells in you. Now if anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, he is not His.\u201d (Romans 8:9)\n\nWho are those who belong to God? If anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, does not belong to God. This means that anyone who has asked Jesus to forgive their sins has had their sins washed by the blood of Jesus and Jesus has come to live within them. If a person is not filled with the Spirit of Christ, they are not a Christian at all.\n\nWe are told in Romans 1:17, \u201c . . the just shall live by faith.\u201d What is faith? Romans 10:17, \u201cFaith comes by hearing and hearing by the word of God.\u201d \n\nThe more we read, understand and apply God\u2019s Word, the more faith we receive. For example, 1 Corinthians 13:4, \u201cLove suffers long (love is patient).\u201d \n\nWhen someone is impatient, it means they are not allowing the love of God to dominate their soul. They must die to self and allow Christ in you, to cause you to be patient.\n", "author": "Come-mistertallyman", "created": 1783267819463, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "CleanUpPhillyTrump24", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Who are those who belong to God?", "last_comment_created": 1783270940314, "content": "<p>\u201cBut you are not in the flesh but in the Spirit, if indeed the Spirit of God dwells in you. Now if anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, he is not His.\u201d (Romans 8:9)</p>\n<p>Who are those who belong to God? If anyone does not have the Spirit of Christ, does not belong to God. This means that anyone who has asked Jesus to forgive their sins has had their sins washed by the blood of Jesus and Jesus has come to live within them. If a person is not filled with the Spirit of Christ, they are not a Christian at all.</p>\n<p>We are told in Romans 1:17, \u201c . . the just shall live by faith.\u201d What is faith? Romans 10:17, \u201cFaith comes by hearing and hearing by the word of God.\u201d</p>\n<p>The more we read, understand and apply God\u2019s Word, the more faith we receive. For example, 1 Corinthians 13:4, \u201cLove suffers long (love is patient).\u201d</p>\n<p>When someone is impatient, it means they are not allowing the love of God to dominate their soul. They must die to self and allow Christ in you, to cause you to be patient.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": 